Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with spoken dialog systems and domain classification, which are both related to natural language processing. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper introduces a neural joint learning model for domain classification and OOD detection, which is a common application of AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves training a model using dynamic class weighting, which is a machine learning technique. 
4. cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with spoken dialog systems, which involve sound processing. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves evaluating the performance of the proposed approach on two domain classification tasks from a large spoken dialogue system, which can be seen as a social network of users interacting with the system.
